caption.body: NOW PLAYING: Born in Lebanon to Palestinian refugees, Imad Khachan, an immigrant without a family, found a way to create his own while operating New York City’s last remaining chess shop as a welcoming place to sit, converse, and create community.  See “King of the Night" by LonelyLeap, now playing in the Video Arts Room located pre-security in the International Terminal. http://bit.ly/2T55gUp
